1. {'key': 'B', 'text': 'end (happening X ends at time T)'}
2. {'key': 'C', 'text': 'give (X gives Y to someone)'}
3. {'key': 'D', 'text': 'close'}

Which option gives the meaning of the word "kind (gufo:Kind, sortal type)"?
0. {'key': 'A', 'text': 'some something is of this kind; it cannot not be of this kind; people can know: it is one something; people can know: it is not two somethings; people can know: it is the same something people saw before.'}
1. {'key': 'B', 'text': 'a thing of one kind; people make things of this kind; it is big: people can be inside it; it can move on the ground; when people are inside it when it moves, they can be in another place, very far, after a short time'}
2. {'key': 'C', 'text': "this something is words. Someone says them to someone else, saying: 'after now I will do something; I know you want it; (because I say this) you can know: after now I will do it.'"}
