1. {'key': 'B', 'text': 'light'}
2. {'key': 'C', 'text': 'broken'}
3. {'key': 'D', 'text': 'water'}

A word whose definition is: "someone's body does something of one kind: the mouth moves, other people can hear something because of it; someone does not do it because this someone wants it: it happens when this someone feels something very good; when other people hear it, they can feel something good". Which word is it?
0. {'key': 'A', 'text': 'animal'}
1. {'key': 'B', 'text': 'mouth'}
2. {'key': 'C', 'text': 'laugh'}
3. {'key': 'D', 'text': 'maker of (X is the maker of Y)'}

Which option gives the meaning of the word "right (of a doable something)"?
0. {'key': 'A', 'text': 'X knew this something before now; because X knew it before, X can think about it now; X knows it now.'}
1. {'key': 'B', 'text': 'an animal of one kind; many of them live with people, in the places where people live; when something happens near it, it does something, people can hear this from far; many people feel something good toward them, they feel something good toward people'}
2. {'key': 'C', 'text': 'a thing of one kind; people make things of this kind; it is not like other things: all its sides are the same; when someone does something to it with the hand, it can move on the ground for some time; children do things with it at many times because it feels good'}
3. {'key': 'D', 'text': "people think like this about this something: 'if someone does it, it is a good something'; people can know: it is a good something."}

Which option gives the meaning of the word "take (X takes Y)"?
0. {'key': 'A', 'text': "if this someone says some words of kind promise, this someone does something after; this someone does not say things of kind lie; other people can think: 'this someone is a good someone'."}
